{"id": "duc04-testb-39:6#18", "contents": "Following the Republican party's underwhelming performance in the recent elections, leaders are re-evaluating their strategy. Senator Trent Lott commented, \"One of the lessons for Republicans out of this is that we need to listen more carefully to the people and we need to have a clear understanding and concise message that we do apply across the nation.\" Both Lott and Gingrich emphasized the importance of tax-cutting and shoring up the Social Security system in the upcoming year. Despite this, many rank-and-file lawmakers are expressing frustration and making phone calls to assess whether to challenge the current Republican leaders."}
